title: File documents for a pending UK patent

heading_context: File documents for a pending UK patent
chunks.html_content:
Use this online service to complete a form or send additional documents for a patent you’ve already applied for (a patent pending).

You need your UK patent application number.
chunks.plain_content:
File documents for a pending UK patent
Use this online service to complete a form or send additional documents for a patent you’ve already applied for (a patent pending).
You need your UK patent application number.

heading_context: File documents for a pending UK patent
chunks.html_content: The service is unavailable from 1am to 3am (UK time) daily.
chunks.plain_content:
File documents for a pending UK patent
The service is unavailable from 1am to 3am (UK time) daily.

heading_context: File documents for a pending UK patent
chunks.html_content:
You can do any of the following online:

  • pay for your patent application (if you did not pay when you applied)
  • provide a statement of inventorship and of right to grant of a patent
  • request a search, supplementary search or further search
  • request a substantive examination
  • pay a grant fee (if the Intellectual Property Office has asked you to)
  • request an extension to a prescribed time limit and upload any supporting document or evidence

You can pay any fees using:

  • a credit or debit card
  • your deposit account with the Intellectual Property Office

heading_context: File documents for a pending UK patent
Documents you can upload
chunks.html_content: You must include a cover letter with any documents you send.
chunks.plain_content:
File documents for a pending UK patent
Documents you can upload
You must include a cover letter with any documents you send.

heading_context: File documents for a pending UK patent
Documents you can upload
chunks.html_content:
To support your patent application you can upload:

  • claims (if not filed with your application)
  • an abstract (if not filed with your application)
  • replacement pages of the specification
  • replacement drawings (in black and white only)
  • amended pages of the specification (pre-grant only)
  • translations of priority documents
  • search reports from other patent offices
  • sequence listings (saved as .txt files)

All documents except sequence listings must be saved as PDFs. This includes the cover letter.

heading_context: File documents for a pending UK patent
Send forms and documents by post
Supporting documents
chunks.html_content:
You can send printed forms and supporting documents by post if you have not already sent them with your application.

You can download and fill in forms for:

  • payment of a patent application fee
  • statement of inventorship and of right to grant of a patent
  • request for a search, supplementary search or further search
  • request for a substantive examination
  • request for a extension to a prescribed time limit

You can send supporting documents for pending patents by post, including:

  • claims (if not filed with your application)
  • an abstract (if not filed with your application)
  • replacement pages of the specification
  • replacement drawings (in black and white only)
  • amended pages of the specification (pre-grant only)
  • translations of priority documents
  • search reports from other patent offices
  • sequence listings
